{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844632189,"sessionID":"ses_28769887affepp6B2AuTTWuCRc","part":{"id":"prt_d7896a2cd001TFq8LfNWmsViM6","messageID":"msg_d789695070017qGyBAuzJ5VmGC","sessionID":"ses_28769887affepp6B2AuTTWuCRc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_39e8567c83c54eeeb1dc23bd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Core Types & Error Definitions\n11: \n12: - [ ] **1.1** Add `DeleteOptions` struct to `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` — fields: GracePeriodSeconds, Force, LabelSelector, Preconditions\n13: - [ ] **1.2** Add `ErrSandboxNotFound`, `ErrDeletionFailed`, `ErrStaleFinalizer`, `ErrOrphanedResource` to `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n14: - [ ] **1.3** Add `WebhookConfig` struct to `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` — fields: URL, Timeout, RetryCount\n15: - [ ] **1.4** Add `AuditLogEntry` struct to `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` — fields: SandboxID, Namespace, Reason, Initiator, Duration, ResourcesCleaned\n16: - [ ] **1.5** Add `DeletionEvent` struct to `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` — fields: Type, Reason, Message, InvolvedObject, Timestamp\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## Phase 2: Deletion Handlers (HTTP Layer)\n21: \n22: - [ ] **2.1** Implement `handleDeleteSandbox` in `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` — DELETE /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/sandboxes/{sessionId}\n23: - [ ] **2.2** Add route registration for sandbox DELETE in server.go (existing agentruntime/codeinterpreter pattern)\n24: - [ ] **2.3** Implement query param binding for DeleteOptions (gracePeriodSeconds, force, labelSelector)\n25: - [ ] **2.4** Add HTTP 404 response for non-existent sandbox (AR-006-004)\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Phase 3: WorkloadManager Interface Extension\n30: \n31: - [ ] **3.1** Add `DeleteSandbox(ctx, namespace, sessionID string, opts DeleteOptions) error` to WorkloadManager interface\n32: - [ ] **3.2** Add `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, namespace, sessionID string) (*Sandbox, error)` to interface\n33: - [ ] **3.3** Add `ListSandboxes(ctx, namespace string, opts ListOptions) (*SandboxList, error)` to interface\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## Phase 4: Graceful Shutdown Implementation\n38: \n39: - [ ] **4.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful.go` — implement `drainConnections(sandboxID)` to stop routing new traffic\n40: - [ ] **4.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful.go` — implement `waitForConnections(sandboxID, timeout)` with context\n41: - [ ] **4.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful.go` — implement `executePreDeleteHook(sandbox, hookConfig)` with timeout\n42: - [ ] **4.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful.go` — implement `sendSIGTERM(podName, namespace)` via exec\n43: - [ ] **4.5** Integrate graceful shutdown into DeleteSandbox flow with gracePeriodSeconds support (AR-006-010)\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## Phase 5: TTL & Expiration Logic\n48: \n49: - [ ] **5.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/expiration.go` — implement `isExpiredByTTL(sandbox)` check\n50: - [ ] **5.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/expiration.go` — implement `isExpiredByIdleTimeout(sandbox)` check\n51: - [ ] **5.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/expiration.go` — implement `isExpiredByMaxLifetime(sandbox)` check\n52: - [ ] **5.4** Add DefaultTTL, DefaultIdleTimeout, DefaultMaxLifetime constants to `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n53: - [ ] **5.5** Implement expiration check in garbage collector loop (AR-006-020, AR-006-021, AR-006-022)\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## Phase 6: Batch Deletion Operations\n58: \n59: - [ ] **6.1** Implement `handleDeleteAllSandboxes` — DELETE /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/sandboxes?deleteAll=true\n60: - [ ] **6.2** Implement `handleDeleteByLabelSelector` — DELETE with labelSelector query param\n61: - [ ] **6.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/batch.go` — implement `deleteStaleSandboxes()` for Unknown/Failed state > 1hr\n62: - [ ] **6.4** Add async deletion support for batch operations > 10 sandboxes\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ## Phase 7: Resource Cleanup\n67: \n68: - [ ] **7.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/cleanup.go` — implement `cleanupServices(namespace, ownerRef)` using ownerReference\n69: - [ ] **7.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/cleanup.go` — implement `cleanupConfigMaps(namespace, ownerRef)` with deletion标记\n70: - [ ] **7.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/cleanup.go` — implement `cleanupPVCs(namespace, ownerRef)` respecting ReclaimPolicy\n71: - [ ] **7.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/cleanup.go` — implement `cleanupOrphanedResources(sandbox)` for AR-006-061\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## Phase 8: Lifecycle Events & Webhooks\n76: \n77: - [ ] **8.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/events.go` — implement `emitDeletionEvent(sandbox, reason)` using k8s event recorder\n78: - [ ] **8.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/events.go` — implement `sendDeletionWebhook(sandbox, config)` with retry (max 3)\n79: - [ ] **8.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/events.go` — implement `logDeletionAudit(entry)` for audit trail\n80: - [ ] **8.4** Integrate events into DeleteSandbox flow\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ## Phase 9: Error Handling & Retry\n85: \n86: - [ ] **9.1** Map new error types to HTTP status codes in `server.go` handleError method\n87: - [ ] **9.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/retry.go` — implement `retryDeletion(ctx, fn, maxRetries)` with exponential backoff\n88: - [ ] **9.3** Add retry logic to garbage collector for transient deletion failures\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ## Phase 10: Integration with AR-005\n93: \n94: - [ ] **10.1** Hook into sandbox creation failure path — call cleanup on rollback\n95: - [ ] **10.2** Use existing k8s_client from AR-005 for all deletion operations\n96: - [ ] **10.3** Integrate with informer watches for sandbox state tracking\n97: - [ ] **10.4** Reuse store's DeleteSandbox/GetSandbox methods\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ## Phase 11: Unit Tests\n102: \n103: - [ ] **11.1** `pkg/workloadmanager/delete_test.go` — TestDeleteSandbox_Success (AR-006-001)\n104: - [ ] **11.2** `pkg/workloadmanager/delete_test.go` — TestDeleteSandbox_NotFound (AR-006-004)\n105: - [ ] **11.3** `pkg/workloadmanager/delete_test.go` — TestDeleteSandbox_ForceDelete (AR-006-003)\n106: - [ ] **11.4** `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful_test.go` — TestDrainConnections (AR-006-012)\n107: - [ ] **11.5** `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful_test.go` — TestExecutePreDeleteHook (AR-006-011)\n108: - [ ] **11.6** `pkg/workloadmanager/expiration_test.go` — TestIsExpired_TTL (AR-006-020)\n109: - [ ] **11.7** `pkg/workloadmanager/expiration_test.go` — TestIsExpired_IdleTimeout (AR-006-021)\n110: - [ ] **11.8** `pkg/workloadmanager/batch_test.go` — TestDeleteAllInNamespace (AR-006-030)\n111: - [ ] **11.9** `pkg/workloadmanager/batch_test.go` — TestDeleteByLabelSelector (AR-006-031)\n112: - [ ] **11.10** `pkg/workloadmanager/events_test.go` — TestEmitDeletionEvent (AR-006-040)\n113: - [ ] **11.11** `pkg/workloadmanager/cleanup_test.go` — TestCleanupServices (AR-006-050)\n114: - [ ] **11.12** `pkg/workloadmanager/cleanup_test.go` — TestCleanupPVCs_RetainPolicy (AR-006-052)\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ## Phase 12: Integration Tests\n119: \n120: - [ ] **12.1** `pkg/workloadmanager/e2e_delete_test.go` — E2E sandbox deletion flow\n121: - [ ] **12.2** E2E graceful shutdown with active connections\n122: - [ ] **12.3** E2E TTL expiration and auto-cleanup\n123: - [ ] **12.4** E2E batch deletion with 100+ sandboxes\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: ## Phase 13: Verification\n128: \n129: - [ ] **13.1** `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` — successful compilation\n130: - [ ] **13.2** `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` — all unit tests pass\n131: - [ ] **13.3** `go test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` — no race conditions\n132: - [ ] **13.4** `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` — no issues\n133: - [ ] **13.5** `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` — linter passes\n134: - [ ] **13.6** Test coverage > 40% (`go test -coverprofile=c.out ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`)\n135: \n136: ---\n137: \n138: ## Dependency Graph\n139: \n140: | Task | Depends On |\n141: |------|------------|\n142: | Phase 1 | — (standalone) |\n143: | Phase 2 | Phase 1, Phase 3 |\n144: | Phase 3 | Phase 1 |\n145: | Phase 4 | Phase 2 |\n146: | Phase 5 | Phase 1 |\n147: | Phase 6 | Phase 2, Phase 3 |\n148: | Phase 7 | AR-005 (k8s_client) |\n149: | Phase 8 | Phase 1 |\n150: | Phase 9 | Phase 1, Phase 2 |\n151: | Phase 10 | AR-005 complete |\n152: | Phase 11 | Phase 1-10 |\n153: | Phase 12 | Phase 11 |\n154: | Phase 13 | Phase 11-12 |\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ## References\n159: \n160: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md`\n161: - Design: ST-3 completed\n162: - Related AR: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器)\n\n(End of file - total 162 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Core Types & Error Definitions\n\n- [ ] **1.1** Add `DeleteOptions` struct to `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` — fields: GracePeriodSeconds, Force, LabelSelector, Preconditions\n- [ ] **1.2** Add `ErrSandboxNotFound`, `ErrDeletionFailed`, `ErrStaleFinalizer`, `ErrOrphanedResource` to `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n- [ ] **1.3** Add `WebhookConfig` struct to `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` — fields: URL, Timeout, RetryCount\n- [ ] **1.4** Add `AuditLogEntry` struct to `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` — fields: SandboxID, Namespace, Reason, Initiator, Duration, ResourcesCleaned\n- [ ] **1.5** Add `DeletionEvent` struct to `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` — fields: Type, Reason, Message, InvolvedObject, Timestamp\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Deletion Handlers (HTTP Layer)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775844632155,"end":1775844632187}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844632192,"sessionID":"ses_28769887affepp6B2AuTTWuCRc","part":{"id":"prt_d78969eb6001lharZCWKzQXO58","messageID":"msg_d789695070017qGyBAuzJ5VmGC","sessionID":"ses_28769887affepp6B2AuTTWuCRc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_f28d747a1beb48c7b73e2d39","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management features in `pkg/workloadmanager`. This includes cleanup of expired sandboxes, graceful termination, force deletion, and lifecycle hooks.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-006\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Depends On**: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器)\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Scenario: Sandbox Deletion\n18: \n19: ### AR-006-001: Delete Sandbox by SessionID\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** an existing sandbox with known SessionID\n22: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{sessionId}`\n23: - **THEN** the handler SHALL locate the sandbox by SessionID\n24: - **AND** SHALL initiate Pod termination\n25: - **AND** SHALL clean up associated resources (services, configmaps)\n26: - **AND** SHALL remove the sandbox from the store\n27: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with deletion confirmation\n28: \n29: ### AR-006-002: Delete Sandbox by Name\n30: \n31: - **GIVEN** an existing sandbox with known name\n32: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/name/{name}`\n33: - **THEN** the handler SHALL locate the sandbox by name\n34: - **AND** SHALL perform the same cleanup as AR-006-001\n35: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n36: \n37: ### AR-006-003: Force Delete Sandbox\n38: \n39: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with terminating Pod that fails to stop gracefully (stuck in Terminating state > 5 minutes)\n40: - **WHEN** a DELETE request includes `gracePeriodSeconds=0` and `force=true`\n41: - **THEN** the handler SHALL forcefully delete the Pod using DeleteOptions\n42: - **AND** SHALL bypass finalizers if necessary\n43: - **AND** SHALL clean up all associated resources\n44: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n45: \n46: ### AR-006-004: Delete Non-existent Sandbox\n47: \n48: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n49: - **WHEN** a DELETE request targets a non-existent sandbox\n50: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n51: - **AND** SHALL include error message \"sandbox not found\"\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## Scenario: Graceful Shutdown\n56: \n57: ### AR-006-010: Graceful Termination with Draining\n58: \n59: - **GIVEN** a running sandbox with active connections\n60: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is received with `gracePeriodSeconds=30`\n61: - **THEN** the handler SHALL send SIGTERM to the sandbox process\n62: - **AND** SHALL wait for grace period before force termination\n63: - **AND** SHALL allow in-flight requests to complete\n64: - **AND** SHALL reject new requests during grace period\n65: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK only after termination completes or grace period expires\n66: \n67: ### AR-006-011: Pre-delete Hook\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with pre-delete lifecycle hook configured\n70: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is received\n71: - **THEN** the handler SHALL execute the pre-delete hook\n72: - **AND** SHALL wait for hook to complete (max 30 seconds)\n73: - **AND** SHALL proceed with deletion regardless of hook result\n74: - **AND** SHALL log hook execution status\n75: \n76: ### AR-006-012: Connection Draining\n77: \n78: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with active connections\n79: - **WHEN** graceful termination is initiated\n80: - **THEN** the handler SHALL stop routing new traffic to the sandbox\n81: - **AND** SHALL wait for existing connections to close (max grace period)\n82: - **AND** SHALL return \"draining\" status during the grace period\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## Scenario: TTL and Expiration\n87: \n88: ### AR-006-020: Sandbox TTL Enforcement\n89: \n90: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with TTL set to 1 hour\n91: - **WHEN** the sandbox exceeds its TTL\n92: - **THEN** the garbage collector SHALL automatically delete the sandbox\n93: - **AND** SHALL emit an event for TTL expiration\n94: - **AND** SHALL clean up all associated resources\n95: - **AND** SHALL log the expiration for auditing\n96: \n97: ### AR-006-021: Idle Timeout\n98: \n99: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with IdleTimeout set to 10 minutes\n100: - **WHEN** no requests are received for 10 minutes\n101: - **THEN** the garbage collector SHALL mark the sandbox as idle\n102: - **AND** SHALL terminate idle sandboxes based on idle timeout policy\n103: - **AND** SHALL support both immediate deletion and graceful draining for idle sandboxes\n104: \n105: ### AR-006-022: Max Lifetime\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with MaxLifetime set to 24 hours\n108: - **WHEN** the sandbox exceeds MaxLifetime\n109: - **THEN** the garbage collector SHALL reject new requests\n110: - **AND** SHALL terminate the sandbox after current requests complete\n111: - **AND** SHALL ensure sandboxes do not run indefinitely\n112: \n113: ---\n114: \n115: ## Scenario: Batch Operations\n116: \n117: ### AR-006-030: Delete All Sandboxes in Namespace\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** multiple sandbox instances in a namespace\n120: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` with `deleteAll=true`\n121: - **THEN** the handler SHALL delete all sandboxes in the namespace\n122: - **AND** SHALL return the count of deleted sandboxes\n123: - **AND** SHALL support async deletion for large batches\n124: \n125: ### AR-006-031: Delete Sandboxes by Label Selector\n126: \n127: - **GIVEN** multiple sandbox instances with various labels\n128: - **WHEN** a DELETE request includes `labelSelector=app=foo`\n129: - **THEN** the handler SHALL delete only sandboxes matching the label selector\n130: - **AND** SHALL return the count of deleted sandboxes\n131: \n132: ### AR-006-032: Delete Stale Sandboxes\n133: \n134: - **GIVEN** sandboxes in \"Unknown\" or \"Failed\" state for > 1 hour\n135: - **WHEN** the garbage collector runs\n136: - **THEN** the handler SHALL identify stale sandboxes\n137: - **AND** SHALL automatically clean up stale sandboxes\n138: - **AND** SHALL emit events for stale sandbox cleanup\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## Scenario: Lifecycle Events\n143: \n144: ### AR-006-040: Emit Deletion Event\n145: \n146: - **GIVEN** a sandbox is deleted\n147: - **THEN** the handler SHALL emit a Kubernetes Event\n148: - **AND** SHALL include deletion reason, initiated by, and timestamp\n149: \n150: ### AR-006-041: Webhook Notification on Deletion\n151: \n152: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with deletion webhook configured\n153: - **THEN** the handler SHALL send POST notification to the webhook URL\n154: - **AND** SHALL include sandbox metadata in the request body\n155: - **AND** SHALL retry up to 3 times on failure\n156: - **AND** SHALL proceed with deletion regardless of webhook response\n157: \n158: ### AR-006-042: Deletion Audit Log\n159: \n160: - **GIVEN** a sandbox deletion operation\n161: - **THEN** the handler SHALL log:\n162:   - Sandbox identifier (SessionID, name)\n163:   - Namespace\n164:   - Deletion reason (explicit, TTL, idle, stale)\n165:   - Initiator (user, system)\n166:   - Duration from deletion request to completion\n167:   - Resources cleaned up\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## Scenario: Resource Cleanup\n172: \n173: ### AR-006-050: Cleanup Associated Services\n174: \n175: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with associated Services\n176: - **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n177: - **THEN** the handler SHALL delete all Services owned by the sandbox\n178: - **AND** SHALL use ownerReference for automatic cleanup verification\n179: \n180: ### AR-006-051: Cleanup ConfigMaps and Secrets\n181: \n182: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with injected ConfigMaps or Secrets\n183: - **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n184: - **THEN** the handler SHALL delete ConfigMaps if marked for deletion\n185: - **AND** SHALL NOT delete Secrets (they may be shared)\n186: - **AND** SHALL log cleanup actions\n187: \n188: ### AR-006-052: Cleanup PVCs\n189: \n190: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with PVCs\n191: - **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n192: - **THEN** the handler SHALL handle PVC cleanup based on ReclaimPolicy\n193: - **AND** SHALL delete PVCs with ReclaimPolicy=Delete\n194: - **AND** SHALL retain PVCs with ReclaimPolicy=Retain\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: ## Scenario: Error Handling\n199: \n200: ### AR-006-060: Deletion Failure Handling\n201: \n202: - **GIVEN** a sandbox deletion request\n203: - **WHEN** the Kubernetes API returns an error during deletion\n204: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return appropriate HTTP status code\n205: - **AND** SHALL include error message with cause details\n206: - **AND** SHALL log the error for debugging\n207: - **AND** SHALL retry deletion up to 3 times for transient errors\n208: \n209: ### AR-006-061: Orphaned Resource Cleanup\n210: \n211: - **GIVEN** a sandbox whose Pod was deleted externally\n212: - **WHEN** the garbage collector detects the orphan\n213: - **THEN** the handler SHALL clean up the sandbox record\n214: - **AND** SHALL clean up any orphaned Services or ConfigMaps\n215: - **AND** SHALL emit an event for orphan cleanup\n216: \n217: ### AR-006-062: Finalizer Handling\n218: \n219: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with finalizers\n220: - **WHEN** deletion is requested\n221: - **THEN** the handler SHALL execute all finalizers\n222: - **AND** SHALL remove finalizer only after successful execution\n223: - **AND** SHALL handle stuck finalizers with force deletion\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## References\n228: \n229: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md`\n230: - Related AR: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器)\n231: - Sandbox CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n232: - Garbage Collector: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n233: - API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n(End of file - total 233 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management features in `pkg/workloadmanager`. This includes cleanup of expired sandboxes, graceful termination, force deletion, and lifecycle hooks.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-006\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Depends On**: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器)\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Sandbox Deletion\n\n### AR-006-001: Delete Sandbox by SessionID\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775844632151,"end":1775844632190}}}}
