{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775844638969,"sessionID":"ses_28769887affepp6B2AuTTWuCRc","part":{"id":"prt_d7896c0f5001vcMCEJcluqK7ZO","messageID":"msg_d7896b73f001n1fRk7hbSDJTfp","sessionID":"ses_28769887affepp6B2AuTTWuCRc","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775844639613,"sessionID":"ses_28769887affepp6B2AuTTWuCRc","part":{"id":"prt_d7896c254001pQMybNNzNX1mNq","messageID":"msg_d7896b73f001n1fRk7hbSDJTfp","sessionID":"ses_28769887affepp6B2AuTTWuCRc","type":"text","text":"Now I'll create the two required files for the change scaffold:","time":{"start":1775844639610,"end":1775844639610}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844696938,"sessionID":"ses_28769887affepp6B2AuTTWuCRc","part":{"id":"prt_d7896c37c001Qo1zIXi5QFwNvJ","messageID":"msg_d7896b73f001n1fRk7hbSDJTfp","sessionID":"ses_28769887affepp6B2AuTTWuCRc","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_731372d848e84cdabf7a8c2f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Kubernetes Reconciler controller in `pkg/workloadmanager`. The Reconciler is responsible for watching and reconciling Sandbox custom resources with actual Kubernetes resources (Pods, Services, ConfigMaps), ensuring the desired state matches the actual cluster state.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-007\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n- **Depends On**: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器), AR-006 (Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理)\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Reconciler Core Loop\n\n### AR-007-001: Reconciler Startup\n\n- **GIVEN** the workloadmanager service starting\n- **WHEN** the Reconciler is initialized\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL register a Controller for Sandbox resources\n- **AND** SHALL start informers for Sandbox, Pod, Service, ConfigMap resources\n- **AND** SHALL start the reconciliation loop with a worker pool\n- **AND** SHALL log startup status and configuration\n\n### AR-007-002: Reconcile Create Event\n\n- **GIVEN** a new Sandbox CR is created in the cluster\n- **WHEN** the Reconciler receives a Create event\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL fetch the Sandbox object\n- **AND** SHALL validate the Sandbox spec\n- **AND** SHALL create the corresponding Pod resource\n- **AND** SHALL create associated Services (if needed)\n- **AND** SHALL create associated ConfigMaps (if needed)\n- **AND** SHALL update Sandbox status to Running\n- **AND** SHALL set ownerReference for all created resources\n\n### AR-007-003: Reconcile Update Event\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing Sandbox with modifications to spec\n- **WHEN** the Reconciler receives an Update event\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL detect changed fields\n- **AND** SHALL update the Pod with new specifications (image, env, resources)\n- **AND** SHALL update Services if needed\n- **AND** SHALL update ConfigMaps if needed\n- **AND** SHALL log all reconciliation actions\n\n### AR-007-004: Reconcile Delete Event\n\n- **GIVEN** a Sandbox CR is deleted\n- **WHEN** the Reconciler receives a Delete event\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL perform final cleanup\n- **AND** SHALL ensure all owned resources are deleted\n- **AND** SHALL handle cascade deletion via ownerReferences\n\n### AR-007-005: Periodic Reconciliation\n\n- **GIVEN** a running Reconciler\n- **WHEN** the periodic sync interval elapses (default 30 seconds)\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL scan all Sandboxes\n- **AND** SHALL verify actual cluster state matches desired state\n- **AND** SHALL repair any drift detected\n- **AND** SHALL update Sandbox status with current state\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Error Handling & Retry\n\n### AR-007-010: Retry on Transient Errors\n\n- **GIVEN** a reconciliation fails due to transient error (API server temporarily unavailable)\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL retry with exponential backoff\n- **AND** SHALL retry up to 5 times with increasing delays (1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, 16s)\n- **AND** SHALL log each retry attempt\n- **AND** SHALL update Sandbox status to reflect reconciliation failure after max retries\n\n### AR-007-011: Permanent Error Handling\n\n- **GIVEN** a reconciliation fails due to permanent error (invalid spec, insufficient resources)\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL NOT retry\n- **AND** SHALL set Sandbox status to Failed\n- **AND** SHALL add a condition with error details\n- **AND** SHALL emit a Kubernetes Event for the failure\n\n### AR-007-012: Conflict Handling\n\n- **GIVEN** a reconciliation detects resource version conflict\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL fetch the latest version\n- **AND** SHALL re-apply the desired state\n- **AND** SHALL log the conflict resolution\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Resource Synchronization\n\n### AR-007-020: Pod Status Sync\n\n- **GIVEN** a Sandbox with a managed Pod\n- **WHEN** the Pod status changes (Pending, Running, Succeeded, Failed, Unknown)\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL sync Pod status to Sandbox status\n- **AND** SHALL update Sandbox conditions (PodReady, ContainersReady)\n- **AND** SHALL record Pod restart count and container states\n\n### AR-007-021: Service Discovery Sync\n\n- **GIVEN** a Sandbox with managed Services\n- **WHEN** Service endpoints change\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL update Sandbox status with endpoint info\n- **AND** SHALL track ready replicas\n\n### AR-007-022: Orphan Resource Detection\n\n- **GIVEN** a Pod/Service/ConfigMap with ownerReference to a non-existent Sandbox\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL log a warning\n- **AND** SHALL consider implementing automatic cleanup for orphaned resources\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Scaling & Performance\n\n### AR-007-030: Parallel Reconciliation\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple Sandbox resources needing reconciliation\n- **WHEN** the worker pool has multiple workers\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL process multiple Sandboxes in parallel\n- **AND** SHALL limit concurrent reconciles per namespace (default: 10)\n- **AND** SHALL use workqueue for rate limiting\n\n### AR-007-031: Reconcile Rate Limiting\n\n- **GIVEN** high reconciliation frequency\n- **WHEN** the queue depth exceeds threshold\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL implement rate limiting\n- **AND** SHALL use bucket4j or similar for rate limiting\n- **AND** SHALL prioritize critical operations (delete > update > create)\n\n### AR-007-032: Efficient Informers\n\n- **GIVEN** large number of Sandbox resources\n- **WHEN** the Reconciler starts\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL use indexed informers\n- **AND** SHALL filter by namespace when possible\n- **AND** SHALL use label selectors to reduce unnecessary reconciles\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Status & Conditions\n\n### AR-007-040: Status Conditions\n\n- **GIVEN** a Sandbox resource\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL maintain status.conditions:\n  - **PodScheduled**: boolean indicating if Pod is scheduled\n  - **ContainersReady**: boolean indicating if all containers are ready\n  - **Initialized**: boolean indicating if init containers completed\n  - **Reconciled**: boolean indicating if reconciliation succeeded\n  - **Failed**: boolean with reason if reconciliation failed\n\n### AR-007-041: Status Phase\n\n- **GIVEN** a Sandbox resource\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL set status.phase:\n  - **Pending**: Sandbox created, reconciliation in progress\n  - **Running**: Pod is running and ready\n  - **Succeeded**: Pod completed successfully\n  - **Failed**: Pod failed or reconciliation failed\n  - **Unknown**: Unable to determine state\n\n### AR-007-042: Status Metrics\n\n- **GIVEN** a running Reconciler\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL expose Prometheus metrics:\n  - `sandbox_reconcile_total{result=\"success|failure\"}`\n  - `sandbox_reconcile_duration_seconds`\n  - `sandbox_reconcile_retries_total`\n  - `sandbox_workqueue_depth`\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Testing & Observability\n\n### AR-007-050: Reconcile Logging\n\n- **GIVEN** reconciliation operations\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL log:\n  - Reconciliation trigger (create/update/periodic/delete)\n  - Sandbox identifier (name, namespace, UID)\n  - Actions taken (created/updated/deleted resources)\n  - Errors encountered\n  - Duration of reconciliation\n\n### AR-007-051: Structured Error Messages\n\n- **GIVEN** reconciliation errors\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL provide structured error info:\n  - Error code\n  - Resource that caused the error\n  - Suggested action for resolution\n  - Relevant CRD fields\n\n### AR-007-052: Health Checks\n\n- **GIVEN** a running workloadmanager service\n- **WHEN** health check endpoint is called\n- **THEN** the Reconciler SHALL report:\n  - Informer sync status (synced/not synced)\n  - Workqueue depth\n  - Last reconciliation timestamp\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md`\n- Related AR: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器), AR-006 (Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理)\n- Kubernetes Controller Pattern: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/architecture/controller/\n- Controller Runtime: https://book.kubebuilder.io/cronjob-tutorial/controller-overview.html\n- Sandbox CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775844696918,"end":1775844696937}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844696942,"sessionID":"ses_28769887affepp6B2AuTTWuCRc","part":{"id":"prt_d7897292a001O9pz3NGNoiacmH","messageID":"msg_d7896b73f001n1fRk7hbSDJTfp","sessionID":"ses_28769887affepp6B2AuTTWuCRc","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_fd467c7e83b54017b2083782","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L  \n**Stage:** ST-1 (Init)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Reconciler Framework Setup\n\n- [ ] **1.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/reconciler.go` — define Reconciler struct with client, scheme, log\n- [ ] **1.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/reconciler.go` — implement `Reconcile(ctx, req)` method\n- [ ] **1.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/reconciler.go` — implement `SetupWithManager(mgr)` for controller runtime\n- [ ] **1.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/suite_test.go` — setup test environment with envtest\n- [ ] **1.5** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/reconciler_suite_test.go` — basic reconcile test\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Informers & Client Setup\n\n- [ ] **2.1** Add k8s client initialization in `pkg/workloadmanager/client.go` — clientset for Sandbox, Pod, Service, ConfigMap\n- [ ] **2.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/informers.go` — setup informers for Sandbox, Pod, Service, ConfigMap\n- [ ] **2.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/informers.go` — implement indexers for efficient lookups\n- [ ] **2.4** Add `NewReconciler(clusterClient, client, log, scheme)` factory function\n- [ ] **2.5** Verify k8s client connectivity in unit tests\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Create Reconciliation\n\n- [ ] **3.1** Implement `reconcileCreate` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/create.go` — fetch Sandbox and validate spec\n- [ ] **3.2** Implement `createPod` — create Pod with ownerReference to Sandbox\n- [ ] **3.3** Implement `createServices` — create Services if specified in Sandbox spec\n- [ ] **3.4** Implement `createConfigMaps` — create ConfigMaps if specified\n- [ ] **3.5** Update Sandbox status to Running after successful creation\n- [ ] **3.6** Handle partial creation failures with cleanup\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: Update Reconciliation\n\n- [ ] **4.1** Implement `reconcileUpdate` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/update.go` — detect changed fields using resourceVersion\n- [ ] **4.2** Implement `updatePod` — patch Pod with new spec (image, env, resources)\n- [ ] **4.3** Implement `updateServices` — patch Services if spec changed\n- [ ] **4.4** Implement `updateConfigMaps` — patch ConfigMaps if spec changed\n- [ ] **4.5** Add field-level diff logging for debugging\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: Delete Reconciliation\n\n- [ ] **5.1** Implement `reconcileDelete` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/delete.go` — handle final cleanup\n- [ ] **5.2** Implement `cleanupOwnedResources` — delete Pods, Services, ConfigMaps with ownerReference\n- [ ] **5.3** Verify cascade deletion works via ownerReferences\n- [ ] **5.4** Handle stuck resources that fail to delete\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: Periodic Sync\n\n- [ ] **6.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/sync.go` — implement periodic reconciliation\n- [ ] **6.2** Add sync interval configuration (default 30s) to config\n- [ ] **6.3** Implement `syncAllSandboxes` — scan and reconcile all Sandboxes\n- [ ] **6.4** Add drift detection — compare desired state vs actual cluster state\n- [ ] **6.5** Implement `repairDrift` — fix any state mismatches\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7: Status & Conditions\n\n- [ ] **7.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/status.go` — implement `updateStatusConditions`\n- [ ] **7.2** Implement Pod status sync — map Pod conditions to Sandbox conditions\n- [ ] **7.3** Implement status phase management — Pending/Running/Succeeded/Failed/Unknown\n- [ ] **7.4** Add `setStatusPhase(phase)` helper\n- [ ] **7.5** Add condition helpers: `setCondition(type, status, reason, message)`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 8: Error Handling & Retry\n\n- [ ] **8.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/errors.go` — define reconciler error types\n- [ ] **8.2** Implement exponential backoff retry in `reconcileWithRetry`\n- [ ] **8.3** Handle transient errors: retry up to 5 times\n- [ ] **8.4** Handle permanent errors: set Failed status, emit event, no retry\n- [ ] **8.5** Implement conflict handling: fetch latest, re-apply\n\n---\n\n## Phase 9: Event Recording\n\n- [ ] **9.1** Integrate k8s event recorder in Reconciler\n- [ ] **9.2** Emit events for: Create success/failure, Update, Delete, Retry\n- [ ] **9.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/events.go` — event emission helpers\n- [ ] **9.4** Add event filtering to avoid duplicate events\n\n---\n\n## Phase 10: Workqueue & Rate Limiting\n\n- [ ] **10.1** Setup workqueue with rate limiting in `SetupWithManager`\n- [ ] **10.2** Configure bucket4j rate limiter: burst 10, rate 10 QPS\n- [ ] **10.3** Implement priority: delete > update > create\n- [ ] **10.4** Add namespace-scoped rate limiting\n- [ ] **10.5** Implement max concurrent reconciles per namespace (default 10)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 11: Metrics & Observability\n\n- [ ] **11.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/metrics.go` — define Prometheus metrics\n- [ ] **11.2** Add `sandbox_reconcile_total` counter with labels\n- [ ] **11.3** Add `sandbox_reconcile_duration_seconds` histogram\n- [ ] **11.4** Add `sandbox_reconcile_retries_total` counter\n- [ ] **11.5** Add `sandbox_workqueue_depth` gauge\n- [ ] **11.6** Expose metrics endpoint in workloadmanager\n\n---\n\n## Phase 12: Health Checks\n\n- [ ] **12.1** Implement `/healthz/reconciler` health check endpoint\n- [ ] **12.2** Check informer sync status\n- [ ] **12.3** Report workqueue depth\n- [ ] **12.4** Report last reconciliation timestamp\n\n---\n\n## Phase 13: Unit Tests\n\n- [ ] **13.1** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/create_test.go` — TestReconcileCreate_Success\n- [ ] **13.2** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/create_test.go` — Tes